LEPLAY? I am intrigued by the new rules/restrictions, and would find it an interesting challenge. <br><br>Whytspirit Mystreaver<br>36 season Shaman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/umekora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mekora</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(10/10/01 5:34:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Role Play Server</span><hr size=1> Things will definitely settle down in probably a week or so when people get to a high enough level that the trivial loot code and grouping restrictions actually affect them, or when they just miss their high-level characters on their old servers.  I predict that the majority, not all but most, of the people who stay actually will roleplay, but right now the language barrier is making that difficult for people in areas with mixed populations (EC, for one).<br><br>I've moved to the new server and intend to stay there, for a variety of reasons.  I'm not deleting any of my characters on Quellious and don't intend to, but I don't think I'll be going back anytime soon.<br><br>If anyone knows Theodinn or anyone from Knights of the Ebony Blade, please tell them Merteuil will likely not be back for a while if at all, I have every confidence that he will choose someone perfectly capable to replace her if he has not done so already.<br><br>Mekora/Merteuil/etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugurunt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gurunt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(10/10/01 6:36:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Role Play Server</span><hr size=1> <br>Well, the #1 thing needed in a working role play server is an active GM to police grief players or people who generally just don't roleplay (doodspeakers, people who will flood /auction as a secondary chat channel ect)....<br><br>So, trust in Verant's customer service to make your roleplaying experience on Firona Vie the best it can be!<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ulaigor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laigor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(10/11/01 9:18:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> what about non cleric races</span><hr size=1> I think it will be interesting when people get to the really high raid levels- how is a poor ogre/troll/barbarian/iskar to get a rez? Hopefully those will not be limited by religions/alignment so that some evil cleric can rez the poor buggers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/umaevepalantiri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maeve Palantiri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(10/11/01 1:51:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what about non cleric races</span><hr size=1> rezzing is by 'alignment' not by 'team' the rp server isn't a 'team' server<br><br>Maeve <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ulaigor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laigor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(10/11/01 2:54:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Teams?</span><hr size=1> Where did you get the &quot;team&quot; that you are emphasizing out of my post? <br>   I will expand on my thought since you seem think i was talking about teams. I know that they are basing the rezz/poss bonus spells on alignment-hence saying I hope some evil cleric can rez the poor buggers( I know barbarians are not evil- so i will not be elaborating on that also), and I am sure there is someway that they can be rezzed. I was just bringing up courious points of interest to me personally that put a nice twist into the game.<br>   MY POINT once again is that these races do not have a class that can rez at all,  although I know some religion/alignments from cleric classes overlap- therefore it will be INTERESTING to see what happens in the high end of a server like this.  Key word to my post was intersting, I guess i will have to elaborate on all my thoughts from now on so they dont get mis-interpreted or used against me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/umekora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mekora</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></s